# SMTP Configuration for Email Sending
# Choose one of the following providers and fill in the details

# Option 1: Gmail (Personal use / Testing)
# 1. Go to Google Account > Security > 2-Step Verification > Turn On
# 2. Go to Google Account > Security > App Passwords > Create specific app password
# 3. Use that 16-character password below (remove spaces)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your_email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your_16_char_app_password
SMTP_SECURE=false # Set to true if using port 465
SMTP_FROM="CookFlow <your_email@gmail.com>"

# Option 2: Resend (Recommended for Production)
# 1. Sign up at https://resend.com
# 2. Create an API Key
# 3. Verify your domain (optional for testing, mandatory for production)
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.resend.com
# SMTP_PORT=465
# SMTP_USER=resend
# SMTP_PASS=re_123456789
# SMTP_SECURE=true
# SMTP_FROM="CookFlow <onboarding@resend.dev>"

# Option 3: Ethereal Email (Fake emails for testing)
# 1. Visit https://ethereal.email/create
# 2. Copy the configuration provided
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.ethereal.email
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=your_ethereal_user
# SMTP_PASS=your_ethereal_pass
